    <section id="id10478568">
      <title>Memorandum</title>
      <para id="id10597262">The educator must help the learners to obtain the information on their birthdays in class so that they can complete the bar graph.</para>
      <para id="id3788655">Let the learners raise their hands to show in which month their birthdays are. Count how many learners have birthdays in that month. The learners write this information in the circle above each month.</para>
      <para id="id4011954">for example: three children have their birthdays in January. The 3 is written in the circle above Jan. </para>
      <para id="id10618828">This can be a class activity.</para>
      <para id="id10401263">It is also a good opportunity to learn the names of the months in the correct sequence. It is not required of them to write the names of the months at this stage.</para>
      <para id="id12889959">Give the learners enough time to discuss their findings, make deductions and draw conclusions after they have completed the bar graph.</para>
      <para id="id4824730"/>
    </section>
